JOHANNESBURG - The SABC has announced it's reviewing its 2004 editorial policies.
	
	The broadcaster will hold public hearings in all nine provinces. The SABC started a process to revise these policies in 2013. READ: SABC defends editorial policy to MPs The Independent Communications Authority later rejected this document, because -- among other things -- it banned the airing of violent protest footage. The 2004 policy thus stands. The deadline for written submissions is 31 August. eNCA